Don’t regret not getting those wheels ceramic coated! Best way to keep matte or satin wheels clean? Ceramic coating 100%. Main reason they are so hard to keep clean as they’re porous, trapping in dirt and grime. Applying the ceramic will create less surface tension, making the cleaning process so much easier and not get dirtier as fast!

Aquatek ceramic/glass coating stands out from other coatings due to its unmatched durability and hydrophobic properties. 🛡️ Unlike traditional coatings, it forms a strong bond with the surface, creating a protective layer that is resistant to scratches, UV rays, and chemical damage. Additionally, its hydrophobic properties lead to water beading and sheeting, preventing water spots and making maintenance effortless. 💧🚫 With its exceptional heat resistance, Aquatek ceramic/glass coating keeps surfaces cool and protected. 🔥 Its long-lasting formula ensures that your vehicle or any other surface remains glossy and protected for years to come, making it truly unlike any other coating available. 🌟

As a quick detailer and waterless wash, it’s perfect for paint, glass, and chrome. With just a few sprays, Triple Threat All-In-One Formula will make your car look like you spent hours cleaning it. It’s perfect for use between full car washes.

Triple Threat All-In-One Formula is engineered for safe, on-the-go cleaning and protection for your vehicle’s exterior surfaces. Given that Triple Threat All-In-One has surfactants and lubricating agents, it is also meant to be used as a lubricant during the clay bar process, as it will prevent marring to the vehicle surface while not degrading the detailing clay like soapy water does. #detailinglife  #detailingcars #detailingproducts #detailingaddicts #detailingstudio
